One part of these structures is named for Janus and Epimethus, while another is associated with Methone. A theory for these structures' formation was proposed by  Édouard Roche, who also names a section between these structures. The existence of gaps in these structures was suggested by Pierre-Simon Laplace. These gaps included those named after Colombo and Maxwell, and the largest is the Cassini Division.
